OL,4,Callowing' baby son's brain injury
OL,6,FWatts claimed Carrie had told her to
OL,7,Fgo back to bed earlier that morning
OL,8,Fadding she felt 'hesitant' at leaving
OL,9,Fher son with him but he reassured her
OL,10,Fit would fine.JBased on their accounts
OL,11,Fthe prosecution stated it was 'likely'
OL,12,FCarrie inflicted the injuries to the
OL,13,Fboy and that Watts 'failed to take
OL,14,Freasonable steps to protect her son'
OL,15,Fgiven her supposed concerns.
OL,17,FCarrie, of Coventry Road, Yardley, and
OL,18,FWatts, of Greenvale, Northfield, will
OL,19,Fbe sentenced on 28 March.
